{
  "text": "For halfspace range searching, one can use Chan's latest results on partition trees to give data structures with t u = O(lg lg n) and t q = O(n 1−1/d ) [CITATION_1] , and with some extra work, one can extend the results in [CITATION_2] to achieve a tradeoff between query time and update time of",
